      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"لَوْ أَنَّ رَجُلاً ضَرَبَ رَجُلاً بِخَزَفَةٍ أَوْ بِآجُرَّةٍ فَمَاتَ كَانَ مُتَعَمِّداً\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5214 - Zarif ibn Naṣih narrated from Ali ibn Abi Hamzah from Abu Basir, who said:\nAbu Abdullah (as) said: \"If a man strikes another man with a piece of pottery or a brick and he dies, it is considered intentional killing.\""
        ]
      }
